    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "<del>\n--location is a shortcut for bypassing IPython's guess about the IP of the machine on which it is running. When you pass ipengine --location=172.16.1.140 you are telling ipengine that *ipengine* is run on the machine 172.16.1.140. ipengine then compares this with the `location` field in the connection file (the controller's IP, and set by ipcontroller --location if you want), and determines that the engine and controller are running on the same machine. Finally, since the controller is listening on all interfaces (*), the engine should use the loopback interface.\n</del>\n\n<del>\nBasically, you told ipengine explicitly that the engine is on the same machine as the controller.\n</del>\n"
  },
