    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "oh, I see. The documentation seems to contradict this. `ipengine -h` gives:\n\n```\n--location=<Unicode> (EngineFactory.location)\n    Default: u''\n    The location (an IP address) of the controller.  This is used for\n    disambiguating URLs, to determine whether loopback should be used to connect\n    or the public address.\n```\n\nAlso this issue persists regardless of how I set `--location`. Leaving it off entirely or setting it to the actual ip address of the machine I'm starting the engine on seems to give the same behavior. Regardless of how I start the engine, it tries to connect to localhost instead of the `location` specified in the url_file. I'll look into it more tomorrow.\n"
  },
