    "updated_at": "2014-04-01T23:23:15Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, IPython needs to know the engine's ip and the controller's ip when the controller is listening on all interfaces. Otherwise, the engine has no way of knowing which ip it should connect to. It's defaulting to localhost when it doesn't know the engine's ips, which is a bit odd. I should probably switch that default to use the external IP instead of loopback.\n"
